Default prompt for regular user:
"$"

Default prompt for root user:
"#"

Example of a default prompt:
"[jake@pine share] $"
    - jake = user
    - pine = computer name
    - share = /usr/share/ - current working directory

Opening Terminal:
- Right-click an empty area on [Desktop] (some distros disable this feature)
- Left-click [Activities] (Left-top corner of Desktop) | Type "terminal", press Enter

Customize Terminal Font/Colors:
- Terminal Panel Icon or 3 Bar Vertical Icon -> [Preferences]
- Profiles (under) -> "Unnamed"
- Text -> Text Appearance
- Colors -> Text and Background Color / Palette

Virtual Consoles:
- Ctrl + Alt + F1 = Login (tty1)
- Ctrl + Alt + F2 = Desktop (tty2)
- Ctrl + Alt + F3 = Console (tty3)
- Ctrl + Alt + F4 = Console (tty4)
- Ctrl + Alt + F5 = Console (tty5)
- Ctrl + Alt + F6 = Console (tty6)
- Ctrl + Alt + F7 = Blank (tty7)